-- 05-meta-cell-designer.cell
-- A Cell program that designs Cell programs. Programs that write programs.
--
-- Tests: В§ quotation as data, вҠўвҲҳ evolution loop, oracle-gated design iteration,
--        proof-carrying computation (design + verify), вҠўвҠў spawner
--
-- Domain: "An automated code review system that checks for security
-- vulnerabilities, suggests fixes, and verifies the fixes don't break
-- existing tests."

вҠў domain
  given description вүЎ "An automated code review system that checks for security vulnerabilities, suggests fixes, and verifies the fixes don't break existing tests."
  yield description

  вҠЁ description is a clear problem domain

вҠў cell-spec
  given spec-path вүЎ "docs/design/cell-v0.1-spec.md"
  yield symbols, execution-model, patterns

  вҠў= symbols вҶҗ "вҠў (declare cell), вҲҙ (soft body), вҠў= (hard body), вҠЁ (oracle), вҠЁ? (recovery), В§ (quotation), В«В» (interpolation), вүЎ (binding), вҶ’ (output access), в–ё (refinement), вҠўвҲҳ (evolution), вҠўвҠў (spawner)"

  вҠў= execution-model вҶҗ "eval-one via Kahn's algorithm: find cells with all givens bound, evaluate one, check oracles, freeze yields. Monotonic вҖ” yields only get bound. Document IS the state."

  вҠў= patterns вҶҗ "proof-carrying computation (LLM finds, code verifies), self-crystallization (вҲҙ вҶ’ вҠў=), evolution loops (вҠўвҲҳ rewrites soft cells), spawners (вҠўвҠў grows frontier), cell-as-agent (inbox вҶ’ dispatch вҶ’ act)"

вҠў decompose
  given domainвҶ’description
  yield components[], dataflow[]

  вҲҙ Analyze В«domainвҶ’descriptionВ» and decompose it into logical components
    for a Cell program. Identify:
    - What inputs the system needs (code diffs, test suites)
    - What processing stages are required (parse, scan, analyze, fix, verify)
    - What outputs the system produces (vulnerability reports, fix suggestions, test results)
    - How data flows between stages (which stage needs which outputs)

    Produce a components list (named processing stages) and a dataflow list
    (pairs of componentвҶ’output connections).

  вҠЁ length(components) вүҘ 4
  вҠЁ each component has a clear single responsibility
  вҠЁ dataflow forms a DAG (no cycles)
  вҠЁ dataflow covers every component (no orphans)

вҠў design-cells
  given decomposeвҶ’components
  given decomposeвҶ’dataflow
  given cell-specвҶ’symbols
  given cell-specвҶ’execution-model
  yield В§program

  вҲҙ Using the Cell language symbols (В«cell-specвҶ’symbolsВ») and execution model
    (В«cell-specвҶ’execution-modelВ»), translate the components
    В«decomposeвҶ’componentsВ» and dataflow В«decomposeвҶ’dataflowВ» into a valid
    Cell program. For each component, write a вҠў cell declaration with:
    - given: inputs from upstream cells (using вҶ’ notation per dataflow)
    - yield: named outputs
    - вҲҙ: natural language instruction for what the cell does
    - вҠЁ: oracle assertions that verify correctness

    Use вҠў= for any cell that can be deterministic (e.g., parsing, formatting).
    Use В§ quotation for cells that inspect other cells' definitions.
    Include at least one вҠўвҠў spawner if the domain requires parallel work
    (e.g., scanning multiple vulnerability categories independently).

  вҠЁ В§program contains only valid Cell syntax
  вҠЁ every component from decomposeвҶ’components has a corresponding вҠў cell
  вҠЁ every dataflow edge from decomposeвҶ’dataflow is expressed via given/вҶ’
  вҠЁ at least one cell uses вҠў= (crystallized)
  вҠЁ at least one cell has вҠЁ oracles

вҠў trace-readiness
  given В§program
  yield ready-order[], blocking-map

  вҲҙ Simulate eval-one scheduling on В«В§programВ». Walk the cell graph:
    1. Find cells with all givens already bound (вүЎ present) вҖ” these are ready
    2. Record which cells are blocked and what they wait for
    3. Determine the evaluation order (topological sort via Kahn's)
    4. Verify no cell is permanently blocked (all paths eventually resolve)

    Output the ready-order (sequence of cell names in execution order) and
    a blocking-map (for each blocked cell, what it waits on).

  вҠЁ ready-order is a valid topological sort of the cell graph
  вҠЁ every cell in В§program appears exactly once in ready-order
  вҠЁ no cell is permanently blocked (all givens are eventually satisfiable)

вҠў simulate-oracles
  given В§program
  given trace-readinessвҶ’ready-order
  yield oracle-results[], awkward-spots[]

  вҲҙ For each cell in В«В§programВ», evaluate its вҠЁ oracle assertions:
    - Can the oracle be checked deterministically? (structural/value check)
    - Does it require LLM judgment? (semantic check)
    - Is the oracle too vague to be useful? (ambiguous)
    - Is the oracle redundant with the вҲҙ body? (tautological)

    Mark each oracle as: deterministic, semantic, ambiguous, or tautological.
    Collect awkward-spots: cells with ambiguous/tautological oracles, cells
    with no oracles, cells whose вҲҙ body is unclear or underspecified.

  вҠЁ oracle-results covers every вҠЁ in В§program
  вҠЁ each oracle-result classifies the oracle type
  вҠЁ awkward-spots identifies genuine design weaknesses

вҠў critique
  given В§program
  given simulate-oraclesвҶ’awkward-spots
  given trace-readinessвҶ’blocking-map
  yield problems[], suggestions[]

  вҲҙ Review В«В§programВ» for design problems:
    1. Awkward oracle spots: В«simulate-oraclesвҶ’awkward-spotsВ»
    2. Missing edges: are there components that should connect but don't?
    3. Crystallization opportunities: which вҲҙ cells could be вҠў= instead?
    4. Missing spawners: does the domain need parallel processing not captured?
    5. Over-specification: are any вҲҙ blocks so detailed they're pseudocode?
    6. Under-specification: are any вҲҙ blocks too vague to execute?

    For each problem, suggest a specific fix.

  вҠЁ length(problems) вүҘ 1 вҲЁ В§program has no design issues
  вҠЁ each problem has a corresponding suggestion
  вҠЁ suggestions are actionable Cell syntax changes

вҠў redesign
  given В§program
  given critiqueвҶ’problems
  given critiqueвҶ’suggestions
  yield В§program'

  вҲҙ Apply the suggestions В«critiqueвҶ’suggestionsВ» to fix the problems
    В«critiqueвҶ’problemsВ» in В«В§programВ». Rewrite affected cells. Preserve the
    overall structure вҖ” only change what needs fixing. Ensure the redesigned
    program still covers the full domain.

  вҠЁ В§program' has same top-level cell names as В«В§programВ» (unless cells were split/merged per suggestions)
  вҠЁ every problem from critiqueвҶ’problems is addressed in В§program'
  вҠЁ В§program' contains only valid Cell syntax

вҠўвҲҳ evolve(design-cells, decomposeвҶ’components, decomposeвҶ’dataflow, cell-specвҶ’symbols, cell-specвҶ’execution-model)
  through critique, redesign
  until length(critiqueвҶ’problems) = 0
  max 3

  -- Each iteration: design-cells produces В§program вҶ’ trace-readiness
  -- checks scheduling вҶ’ simulate-oracles checks oracle quality вҶ’
  -- critique finds problems вҶ’ redesign fixes them вҶ’ redesigned В§program'
  -- replaces design-cells output. Interface frozen, implementation evolves.

вҠў emit-program
  given redesignвҶ’В§program'
  given domainвҶ’description
  yield final-cell-file

  вҲҙ Format В«redesignвҶ’В§program'В» as a complete .cell file with:
    - Header comment describing the domain: В«domainвҶ’descriptionВ»
    - All cell declarations from the program
    - Clean formatting following Cell conventions

    This is the ready-to-run output.

  вҠЁ final-cell-file is valid Cell syntax
  вҠЁ final-cell-file has a descriptive header comment
  вҠЁ final-cell-file addresses the complete domain description
